{"id":"ee78df18-dbd1-42b6-9314-2ccdfc004340","title":"1519/04/20","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"08a3e86a-f715-4051-b88b-60a830e2d919","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Serravezza, April 20th, [1519].","standoffProperties":[{"id":"cf309b89-4a46-44f4-bd04-25381eb340c1","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":14,"value":"66c0edd4-0404-48c9-aa24-f7822ed8919f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"7f95cf59-3f4f-476c-b537-c6d3378c5108","type":"codex/time-reference","start":17,"end":34,"value":"21bb171b-b9f4-4c62-ac33-77eb5497cb61","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"1827c937-7845-447a-97c9-de9ac4226b10","type":"style/superscript","start":25,"end":26,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"dfcb5d69-ccd3-4a29-8cbd-e1117d252f99","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Pietro Urbano,","standoffProperties":[{"id":"58880c13-8f62-4671-8c93-b305b8d8c049","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":15,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"89a79392-f19f-45bb-b3c0-fcec7ddc6d41","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":15,"value":"6bb71c28-64e1-46e0-961e-b755abf660b4","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"1443cc7e-bfad-4935-af71-f977e5b632b5","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"at the sculptor Michelagniolo\u0027s house in","standoffProperties":[{"id":"db7f30fe-9509-4e5c-8fab-2a40df541bed","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":16,"end":28,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"cb577c0e-b34f-4665-8ddd-401b1b408b6f","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":32,"end":36,"value":"e54f1f8a-f8aa-4695-8eed-d3c13d9058a2","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"6846888a-384f-4859-842a-9a1a8f668755","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"10a8056a-5719-4426-9d91-694acade4472","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":7,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"03c2208f-9eae-428c-992e-cc77c4b90fb2","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Pietro,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0Matters have gone exceedingly ill. This morning \u2014 Saturday \u2014 I was about to lower a column with the utmost care, and had provided for every emergency: but when I had let it down\u00A0about fifty braccia one of the rings of the lewis bolt holding the column gave way, with the result that it fell into the river and broke into a hundred pieces. Donato had entrusted the making of the ring in question to the smith Lazzero, a friend of his; and\u00A0as to its being sufficiently strong, to judge from external appearances it seemed strong enough to lift four columns, as it undoubtedly would have been if it had been properly made. But when it broke the rascally trick played upon us became apparent, for the ring was nowhere solid, and there was not so much metal in it as would have sufficed in thickness\u00A0for the ring of a knife handle, so that I marvel it held so long as it did. All who were on the spot had the narrowest of escapes from death, and a\u00A0magnificent block of stone is ruined. I left the ordering of this tackle to Donato during the Carnival, telling him to go to the blacksmiths and see that all the metal used was good and sound: thou seest how he has behaved to me. Then too the blocks of every one of the pulleys he had made for me cracked at the ring while the column was being lowered and are already on the point of giving way: yet they are twice the size of those used at Santa Maria del Fiore, so that if they had been made of sound metal they would have borne any load. But the iron used was crude and defective, and could not possibly have been worse. All this has come about because Donato wished to oblige his own friend, and left him to select the metal, serving me as thou seest. One must have patience. I shall be back for the feste [Easter], and if it please God shall begin work. Salute Francesco Scarfi in my name.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"8f6213d3-e200-4d52-b565-e28666e9d742","type":"style/uppercase","start":0,"end":5,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"6a20e737-317a-48cc-b931-8f2472ab4997","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":5,"value":"1d88bdc0-d9fd-4159-90e7-3e8f43eabbd7","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"bc2efd08-683b-472a-be17-bfb196e60aee","type":"codex/time-reference","start":45,"end":56,"value":"3a49f50d-e8ee-46aa-92ea-028dd9fd2a47","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"c773d9ee-2358-43f6-8a9c-8d1ea165b277","type":"codex/time-reference","start":60,"end":67,"value":"2947a9e9-4fdc-4fc6-a2d8-a3511bbeeb7b","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"92d0e0b0-dd1f-4948-9930-d6f0d533b3bf","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":71,"end":71,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"781214fb-be77-48ee-863d-68040924fb05","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":94,"end":99,"value":"9c808811-4416-4a9c-a813-24fa29d5ea6f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"300690f1-b56e-4ed4-bedd-14b0edac93c8","type":"codex/document-reference","start":100,"end":100,"value":"3a79e7c3-76ce-46d1-bd5a-27aa0dcd19cf","zeroPoint":true,"metadata":[]},{"id":"bd132174-faa1-4bec-a323-e7bdb8b5db58","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":170,"end":170,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"be2f6abc-7566-44b2-90bd-1905b474b738","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":180,"end":181,"value":"9c808811-4416-4a9c-a813-24fa29d5ea6f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"c1007d5e-deb0-48a1-83b8-534410f20a6f","type":"style/italics","start":200,"end":206,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"d83f83fa-9d17-480d-bd22-d7636c83fb40","type":"language","start":200,"end":206,"value":"it","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"b420829c-fedb-48f8-af2b-e8216f5b5597","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":219,"end":223,"value":"0926cd5a-9c5f